Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Yulanda Pei

2023-03-10

My meme

🐶 Golden Retriever
I feared dogs until I saw my friend’s beautiful Golden Retriever named ‘little gray’. This meme reminds me how adorable Golden Retrievers are. ❤ ❤ ❤ 

library(magick)

# Get images form the internet
dog1 <- image_read("https://paradepets.com/.image/ar_1:1%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_1200/MTkxMzY1Nzg4NjczMzIwNTQ2/cutest-dog-breeds-jpg.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)
dog2 <- image_read("https://www.pdinsurance.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/taylor-sondgeroth-ltsKOg_q_Gc-unsplash-1.webp") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# Creat a blank square next to the "dogs image"

blank1 <- image_blank(width = 300,
                      height = 50,
                      color = '#5058A1'
) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I love Golden Retriever",
                 color = '#FFFFFF',
                 gravity = "center",
                 size = 24,
                 font = "Times New Roman")


# Combine images
picture <- c(blank1, dog1, dog2)


# Create Meme
meme <- image_append(picture, stack = TRUE) 
meme


# Save meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png", format = "png")

My animated GIF

💟Jackson Yee (易烊千玺)
‘Jackson Yee’ is a talented Chinese actor, dancer and singer. He received critical acclaim for his performance in Better Days and was the winner of the Best New Actor Award at the 39th Hong Kong Film Awards. The following is a list of films in which he has starred: ❤ ❤ ❤
- Better Days
- A Little Red Flower
- The Battle at Lake Changjin
- Nice View
- Full River Red 

library(magick)


# Get images of Jackson Yee from the website
jackson1 <- image_read("https://wx3.sinaimg.cn/mw1024/006VJhk2ly1gywwu7yn4hj32192eib29.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

jackson2 <- image_read("https://wx4.sinaimg.cn/mw1024/006VJhk2ly1h38u2qnsgxj30xc14nqv5.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

jackson3 <- image_read("https://wx3.sinaimg.cn/mw1024/006VJhk2ly1h38u2t3cd1j30xc14ne81.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

jackson4 <- image_read("https://wx4.sinaimg.cn/mw1024/006VJhk2ly1h38u2yspq3j30xc14n7wh.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)


# Create a vector of Jackson's images
jackson <- c(jackson1, jackson2, jackson3, jackson4)


# Create animations of Jackson's images and save it
animation <- image_animate(jackson, fps=1) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Jackson Yee", 
                 color = "#FFFFFF", 
                 size = 14, 
                 gravity = "southeast") 

animation

image_write(animation, "animation.gif", format = "gif")

Thanks for reviewing my first project!
